The paper is concerned with designing fitness functions for Embedded Evolutionary Robotics, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using unsupervised learning to compute the entropy of the sensori-motor stream generated by the robot controller, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The approach also involves implementing a curiosity instinct and a discovery instinct, which are concepts related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural Networks (cs.NE). Finally, the approach involves optimizing the fitness function using an evolutionary algorithm, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
